tentative name parsec or parse c 04/11/2026

Parse master file table written in C

Initial release and will update shortly such as changing input to accept local system time and then 
converting to UTC for --cutoff. It currently uses UTC (which is -7:00 where I am). This is because 
the MFT uses UTC. Chose c as the job suites it perfectly. The filesize of the parser is 170kb and
the reason I made it is for my qt app that uses MFT features and needed a solution for that.

usage:

optional drive (default C:)
./parser.exe
or
./parser.exe S:
./parser.exe C: --cutoff "2026-03-19 10:13:18"

will output in format:
recordnumber frn parent_frn mtime ctime fileattrib isdir|name|path


optional argument (one max)

search for new files by time (UTC)
--cutoff "2026-03-19 10:13:18" or 2026-03-19T10:13:18

list mft record
--target <recordno>

same as with default usage but better format for parsing for Qt gui will output in format:
recordnumber|frn|parent_frn|mtime|ctime|fileattrib|isdir|name|path
--parse

